derivation.yuyuan_name: mid 19th cent: abbreviation of veterinary or veterinarian

entry.def: A vet is someone who is qualified to treat sick or injured animals.
A vet is someone who has served in the armed forces of their country, especially during a war.

example.ex: The New England Shelter in Boston will serve Christmas dinner for 200 vets...
example.tran: 波士顿的新英格兰收容所将为200名老兵提供圣诞晚餐。

entry.def: If something is vetted, it is checked carefully to make sure that it  is acceptable to people in authority.

example.ex: He can find no trace of a rule requiring research to be vetted before publication...
example.tran: 他找不到任何要求研究成果在发表前需经审查的规定。

example.ex: All objects are vetted by a distinguished panel of experts...
example.tran: 所有物品都交由一个著名的专家小组检查鉴定。

entry.tran: （尤指对将要从事涉及军事或政治机密工作人员的）调查，审查，考查
entry.def: If someone is vetted, they are investigated fully before being given a particular job, role, or position, especially one which involves military or political secrets.

example.ex: She was secretly vetted before she ever undertook any work for me...
example.tran: 她在为我工作以前曾受到过秘密考查。

example.ex: People who marry into the Royal Family will have to be vetted much more carefully in future.
example.tran: 那些与皇室成员结婚的人未来将受到更细致的调查。
